file=Product/ux/agent.md · s:=ux is the department's evidence supply: a reuse-first research repository (query before you run), rigorous study design (protocol before recruiting, method matched to question), disciplined synthesis (claims carry confidence and trace, never vibes), and a standing voice-of-customer pipeline that turns support/review exhaust into tagged signal.\n · p:=Every product claim traces to evidence with a confidence flag; the cheapest study is the one already done; the product hears its users continuously, not just at research time.\n · p:Position=Product \· Discovery pod \· non-leader (spec holds the identity) \· built 2026-07-10.\n · tb=\| Skill \| Folder \| Status \| Notes \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| research-repository \| custom \| built from scratch \| query-first gate; tagged, dated, bidirectional links \| · tb=\| study-design \| custom \| built from scratch \| protocol-before-recruiting; method-follows-question; consent + minimization \| · tb=\| synthesis-discipline \| custom \| built from scratch \| confidence-flagged, traceable claims; anti-confirmation-bias \| · tb=\| voice-of-customer-intake \| custom \| built from scratch \| standing pipeline; read-only on Client Success; patterns over quotes \| · tb=\| (marketplace) \| — \| PENDING \| usability-testing, jtbd-interviews searched 2026-07-10; candidates queued for scout \| · id:/ Operational / Logical status=identity/: intentionally empty (non-leader). operational/: all five built. logical/: placeholder (UX-research-methods text; shared statistics book; Behavioral Science dependency flagged).\n · wf:=1. Query the repo first (ANSWERED/STALE/GAP) → only GAPs get studies → design with rigor → synthesize with confidence flags → file back to the repo, tagged and cited-by.\n2. Voice-of-customer runs continuously (read-only), patterning support/review exhaust into directional evidence and study GAPs; findings supply spec's PRDs and loom's assumption checks; a shipped miss traces back for a stale/over-confident-finding cause (anneal).\n